Substitution gives $\frac{0}{0}$. Multiply by the conjugate:
\[
 \frac{\sqrt{x+9}-3}{x}\cdot\frac{\sqrt{x+9}+3}{\sqrt{x+9}+3}
 = \frac{(x+9)-9}{x(\sqrt{x+9}+3)}
 = \frac{x}{x(\sqrt{x+9}+3)}
 = \frac{1}{\sqrt{x+9}+3}.
\]
Now substitution works:
\[
 \limto{x \to 0}\,\frac{1}{\sqrt{x+9}+3} 
 = \frac{1}{\sqrt{9}+3} = \frac{1}{3+3} = \frac{1}{6}.
\]
